  "texts": [
    "FCL's architecture is particularly effective at managing continuous collision detection, a feature that proves crucial in capturing the nuances of object interactions over time.",
    "Unlike discrete collision detection methods, which evaluate object positions at specific intervals, continuous collision detection ensures an analysis of object trajectories throughout their motion.",
    "This capability detects potential collisions that may occur between the discrete points of evaluation, thereby offering a more granular and accurate depiction of the simulated environment.",
    "The library supports various proximity queries, including separation distance computation and penetration depth estimation.",
    "The hierarchical representations within FCL enable handling of complex geometries, ensuring the scalability and performance of our simulations."
  ],
